"There's no fourth floor!" "There has to be!" - Ah DIT Bolton Street, you Escher maze you
Basically I envisage modern extensions spanning the back of a terrace. Creating new room, circulation, and amenities.
But ownership, cost, planning, plot ratios, insulation, foundations, available green space, heritage, and construction distribution hamper
If modern extensions could span multiple properties, creating larger joined units, then maybe it could work. Some damn vision for once.
Size and accessibility are often why they become storage or empty. Plot ratios often too tight for two doors, or no rear access existing.
I hope this Rural development action plan also comes up with ways to concert above shop residential units to larger units with extensions...
